"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The assertions on lines 7 and 8 are incorrect. The sinc function in numpy is defined as sin(pi*x)/(pi*x). For x=0, sinc(0) is 1, but for x=1, sinc(1) is sin(pi)/pi which is approximately 0, not exactly 0.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n8c8\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], 0), \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n\"\n}"